  7,121,"They declared, “We ˹now˺ believe in the Lord of all worlds—"
  7,122,the Lord of Moses and Aaron.”
  7,123,"Pharaoh threatened, “How dare you believe in him before I give you permission? This must be a conspiracy you devised in the city to drive out its people, but soon you will see"
  7,124,"I will certainly cut off your hands and feet on opposite sides, then crucify you all.”"
  7,125,"They responded, “Surely to our Lord we will ˹all˺ return"
  7,126,"Your rage towards us is only because we believed in the signs of our Lord when they came to us. Our Lord! Shower us with perseverance, and let us die while submitting ˹to You˺.”"
  7,127,"The chiefs of Pharaoh’s people protested, “Are you going to leave Moses and his people free to spread corruption in the land and abandon you and your gods?” He responded, “We will kill their sons and keep their women. We will completely dominate them.”"
  7,128,"Moses reassured his people, “Seek God’s help and be patient. Indeed, the earth belongs to God ˹alone˺. He grants it to whoever He chooses of His servants. The ultimate outcome belongs ˹only˺ to the righteous.”"
  7,129,"They complained, “We have always been oppressed—before and after you came to us ˹with the message˺.” He replied, “Perhaps your Lord will destroy your enemy and make you successors in the land to see what you will do.”"
  7,130,"Indeed, We afflicted Pharaoh’s people with famine and shortage of crops so they might come back ˹to their senses˺"